
CouchDB-Lucene View-Indexer Version
===================================

This is an example indexer capable of indexing via the index-server interface. For this to
work you must download and run the index_server branch of my couchdb github repo at:

    http://github.com/davisp/couchdb/tree/index_server

Download this package and build the jar as such:

    $ git clone git://github.com/davisp/couchdb-lucene.git couchdb-lucene
    $ cd couchdb-lucene
    $ ant

Edit your couchdb's local.ini to look something like: (make sure to change /path/to/)

    ; CouchDB Configuration Settings

    ; Custom settings should be made in this file. They will override settings
    ; in default.ini, but unlike changes made to default.ini, this file won't be
    ; overwritten on server upgrade.

    [couchdb]
    ;max_document_size = 4294967296 ; bytes

    [httpd]
    ;port = 5984
    ;bind_address = 127.0.0.1

    [log]
    level = debug

    [daemons]
    index_servers={couch_index_servers, start_link, []}

    [index_servers]
    fti=/path/to/couchdb-lucene/bin/couchdb-lucene-index

    [httpd_db_handlers]
    _index = {couch_httpd_view, handle_index_req}

Assuming everything worked, you should now be able to query the server with the url:

    http://127.0.0.1:5984/db_name/_index/fti/view_name/map_name?q="query"

